svg element
------------------
SVG, or Scalable Vector Graphics, is an XML-based vector image format for describing two-dimensional graphics

SVG element you can automate only using xpath

Syntax:
--------------
//*[name()='svg']

or

//*[local-name()='svg']
=============================================
Shadow DOM ele
========================
what is Shadow DOM?
----------------------
Whenever DOM is loaded inside another DOM is called Shadow DOM

Logic
----------
main document-->shadow host-->shadow root-->shadow ele


Which element we can called as shadow element?
----------------------------------------
if element is designed with #shadow-root(open) then that element is shadow ele

Parent tag/element for shadow element is shadow root
Parent tag/element for shadow root is shadow host

Shadow dom elements we can automate only using cssSelector

If element design with #shadow-root(closed) we can not automate this element

=====================================
Broken links
-----------------------
<a href="url">link</a>



How to identify broken link
-------------------------------
the link status code if it is 400 and greater than 400 is broken

If link contains href attribute value as null or empty then such link we can not automate


1.link should have href attribute and it should not empty or null
2.only valid link request we can send to the server
3.get status code from server and validate it

