1.Testng
==================

Arguments for test
------------------
1.priority: To run test case in sequence
2.description:to set some description
3.invocationCount: To run test case 

Assertions in Testng
------------------------
Validate current state of the application
1.Hard assertion
2.Soft assertion

When Assertion fail we will get AssertionError
---------------------------------------------

4.timeOut:The maximum number of milliseconds this test should take. 
If it hasn't returned after this time, it will be marked as a FAIL.

5.dependsOnMethods:Apply dependency between test cases

How to test suite
--------------------
Collection of test cases

XML 
TestNG xml file its configuration file for testng Class

<suite>
<test>
<classes>
<class name="">
<method>registerTest</method>.......@Test
</class>
</classes>
</test>
</suite>

6.enabled=false
How to ignore/ disable any test case from current execution
-------------------------------------------------------
1.Using enabled argument
2.Using xml file (include and exclude test)

<class name="com.WebTesting.TestNG.T72_DisableTest">
      <methods>
         <exclude name="testForSearch"></exclude>//disable
         <!--<include name="testForSearch"></include>-->//include test in execution
      </methods>     
      </class>

